## 3. What to Build

### Domain: `lib/domain/otp_gateway/`

**`entities/dispatch_status.dart`**
`enum DispatchStatus { pending, dispatched, failed }`

**`entities/otp_dispatch_command.dart`**
Fields: `commandId` (String), `systemId` (String), `recipientPhoneNumber` (String), `messageBody` (String), `issuedAt` (DateTime), `simSlot` (SimSlot enum: `defaultSlot`, `sim1`, `sim2`), `status` (DispatchStatus, default: `pending`).
`copyWith({DispatchStatus? status})` method.
Docstring on `messageBody`: **"Write-only. Pass to SmsSenderService immediately. Do not store, log, or reference after send() returns. (Invariant 1)"**

**`value_objects/sms_delivery_report.dart`**
Fields: `commandId` (String), `status` (SmsDeliveryStatus: `sent`, `delivered`, `failedNoService`, `failedGeneric`), `reportedAt` (DateTime), `nonce` (String), `signature` (String), `agentPublicKeyId` (String).
No `messageBody` field. No `recipientPhoneNumber` field. Extends `Equatable`.

**`repositories/otp_gateway_repository.dart`**
Failure types: `CommandNotFoundFailure`, `CommandAlreadyDispatchedFailure`, `SmsDispatchFailure(String detail)`, `ReportSubmissionFailure(String detail)`.
Interface methods:
- `Future<Either<OtpGatewayFailure, OtpDispatchCommand>> fetchCommand({required String commandId, required String systemId})`
- `Future<Either<OtpGatewayFailure, void>> submitDeliveryReport({required SmsDeliveryReport report, required String systemId})`

**`use_cases/receive_dispatch_command_use_case.dart`**
Dependencies: `OtpGatewayRepository`, `AuditLogService`.
Calls `repository.fetchCommand()`. Logs `otpDispatchReceived`. Returns the result. Does NOT touch the message body.

**`use_cases/execute_sms_dispatch_use_case.dart`**
Also defines `abstract class SmsSenderService` here (domain interface).
Dependencies: `SmsSenderService`, `SigningService`, `NonceGenerator`, `AuditLogService`.
Sequence:
1. Check `command.status == DispatchStatus.pending` → if not, return `Left(CommandAlreadyDispatchedFailure())`
2. Call `smsSenderService.send(recipientPhoneNumber: ..., messageBody: command.messageBody, simSlot: ...)` — `messageBody` is passed directly; the local reference is not used after this line
3. Generate `nonce`, get `reportedAt`
4. Build canonical signing input from `command_id`, `status`, `reported_at`, `nonce`
5. Call `signingService.sign(...)` → on failure, return `Left(SmsDispatchFailure(...))`
6. Construct `SmsDeliveryReport` and return `Right(report)`

**`use_cases/report_delivery_status_use_case.dart`**
Dependencies: `OtpGatewayRepository`, `AuditLogService`.
Write audit log entry (`otpSmsSent` or `otpSmsFailed`) BEFORE calling `repository.submitDeliveryReport()`. Write a final entry (`otpReportSubmitted`) after. Return the result.

### Infrastructure: `lib/shared/infrastructure/android_sms_sender_service.dart`
Implements `SmsSenderService`. Uses `MethodChannel('com.superadmin.agent/sms_sender')`. Invokes method `'sendSms'` with a map of `recipient`, `body`, `sim_slot`. Maps the string return value to `SmsDeliveryStatus`. On `PlatformException`, returns `SmsDeliveryStatus.failedGeneric`.
Add: `// TODO(phase-5-android): Implement Kotlin MethodChannel handler using SmsManager with sentIntent PendingIntent`

### Data: `lib/data/otp_gateway/`

**`dtos/otp_dispatch_command_dto.dart`**
Maps `GET /v1/otp-commands/{id}` JSON response to `OtpDispatchCommand`. Maps `sim_slot` string values to `SimSlot` enum.

**`remote/otp_gateway_remote_data_source.dart`**
`fetchCommand(String commandId)` — `GET /v1/otp-commands/{commandId}`.
`submitDeliveryReport(SmsDeliveryReport report)` — `POST /v1/otp-commands/{commandId}/report` with body: `command_id`, `status` (string), `reported_at`, `nonce`, `agent_public_key_id`, `signature`. No `messageBody` in the POST body.

**`repositories/otp_gateway_repository_impl.dart`**
Delegates to `OtpGatewayRemoteDataSource`.

### Presentation: `lib/presentation/otp_gateway/cubit/`

**`otp_dispatch_state.dart`**
States: `OtpIdle`, `OtpFetching`, `OtpDispatching`, `OtpDispatched`, `OtpError(String message)`. No state carries `messageBody`.

**`otp_dispatch_cubit.dart`**
Dependencies: `ReceiveDispatchCommandUseCase`, `ExecuteSmsDispatchUseCase`, `ReportDeliveryStatusUseCase`.
`handleCommand({required String commandId, required String systemId})`: orchestrates the three use cases sequentially. Emits appropriate states. Does not hold a reference to `messageBody` — the use case handles it entirely.

### FCM Handler and DI
Create `lib/shared/infrastructure/otp_gateway_fcm_handler.dart`. Implements `CapabilityCommandHandler`. In `handle()`: retrieves `OtpDispatchCubit` from `GetIt`, calls `handleCommand()`.
Update `lib/di/app_module.dart`: replace `// TODO(phase-5)` with OTP module registrations. Register `OtpGatewayFcmHandler` with the FCM router.

